The paper discusses stochastic control problems with imperfect information, which is a common topic in the control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of sensors and algorithms for searching also suggests relevance to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The focus on information entropy as an objective function suggests relevance to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests relevance to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
